value.value: BEL beta-lactamases are class A expanded-spectrum beta-lactamases that are inhibited by clavulanic acid. They are chromosomally encoded and hydrolyze most cephalosporins and aztreonam.
BEL-1 is a beta-lactamase found in Pseudomonas aeruginosa.
BEL-2 is a beta-lactamase found in Pseudomonas aeruginosa.
BEL-3 is a beta-lactamase found in Pseudomonas aeruginosa.

OXY beta-lactamases are chromosomal class A beta-lactamases that are found in Klebsiella oxytoca. At constitutive low levels, OXY beta-lactamases confer resistance to aminopenicillins and carboxypenicillins. At high induced levels,  OXY beta-lactamases confer resistance to penicillins, cephalosporins and aztreonam.
